<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Diorama&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> Lionel Lambourne, <i>Victorian Painting</i>, London, Phaidon Press, 1999; p. 156.</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Lambourne, p. 157.</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.scienceandsociety.co.uk/results.asp?image=10302430&amp;wwwflag=2&amp;imagepos=1" class="external text" title="http://www.scienceandsociety.co.uk/results.asp?image=10302430&amp;wwwflag=2&amp;imagepos=1" rel="nofollow">Science &amp; Society Picture Library: the collections of the Science Museum, the National Railway Museum and the National Museum of Photography, Film &amp; Television</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <span class="languageicon" style="font-size:0.95em; font-weight:bold; color:#555;">(French)</span> <a href="http://www.bry94.fr/sites/bry/fichier/diaporama_diorama.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.bry94.fr/sites/bry/fichier/diaporama_diorama.pdf" rel="nofollow">All about Daguerre's diorama in Bry</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <span class="languageicon" style="font-size:0.95em; font-weight:bold; color:#555;">(French)</span> <a href="http://www.bry94.fr/bry/2308.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.bry94.fr/bry/2308.htm" rel="nofollow">About the diorama on Bry's official website</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
